The proposed mate-control state is \((v_{1,1},0)\in O_{1,0}\). Consequently its mass in the \((1,O_{1,1})\) coordinate is zero, whereas the target coordinate there is one. Thus this arm-changing analogue cannot satisfy \(Aw=b_{\mathrm{LP}}\) in \(\texttt{def:common-selector-feasibility-lp}\). Moreover, it is not a legal arm-\(1\) selector: by definition, every arm-\(1\) integrated calibration law is supported on \(\mathcal U_1\), but \((v_{1,1},0)\in\mathcal U_0\).

